        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> gra is a menu of actions, I don't really see them as semantically different. But either approach is a reversible decision so not a blocker.\n\nNot opposed to having one menu that is a superset of all that, but please keep the option for the separated way to trigger them as they're different kind of actions. `lsp.buf.code_action()` tends to show actions applicable for the whole buffer, or related to the diagnostics under the cursor. `code_lens.run()` runs the code-lens under the cursor - likely without prompt as there is often only 1 action. (In a way, the code-lens virtual-text is already showing the menu/what gets executed)\n\n> (do we enable them by default?).\n\nNo, and with the current client implementation that resolves all lenses in a buffer eagerly they can be very expensive for a language server to compute.",
