        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I think it would make sense to first expose APIs that allow users to retrieve inlay hints, code lenses, and code actions, making it easier for them to implement their own solutions rather than just providing an opinionated default mapping. Inlay hints currently lack a `run` (execute action) functionality, while code lenses lack a `get` (retrieve actions) functionality. \n\nBesides, the existing API naming is somewhat confusing; for example, `completion.get` and `inline_completion.get` are actually \"execute\" operations, whereas `inlay_hint.get` is actually a \"retrieve\" operation.",
            "created_at": "2026-03-24T03:15:07Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/34813#issuecomment-4115086084",
            "id": 4115086084,
